Corpus T
The first development step was to obtain the 'twurl' tool and use it to test correctness of user key and password.
The second step was to test the two comperhensive C++ libraries.
'QTweetLib' requires Qt4, which I was reluctant to install.
'twitcurl' seems to work for a lot of people, but the included demo kept returning 
twitterClient:: twitCurl::accountVerifyCredGet web response:
{"errors":[{"code":89,"message":"Invalid or expired token."}]}
Finally 'birdy' - "a super awesome Twitter API client for Python in just a little under 400 LOC." was selected.
